Preheat your oven to 220°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} into half moons. Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and thinly slice. Cut the @chorizo{60%g} stick in half lengthways, remove the skin and slice into ½cm wide half moons. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Zest the @lime{1}.

Heat a glug of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the chorizo, cook for ~{5%minutes}. Remove from the #pan{}, set aside. Add the onion and pepper to the pan. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g} and @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1/2}, cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the black beans, chorizo, @water{120%ml} and pop on a #lid{}. Reduce the heat to medium, cook for ~{5%minutes}.

Once the 5 mins is up, remove the lid from your pan. Simmer until the liquid has almost evaporated, ~{3-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Roughly mash the mixture with a #potato masher{}. Stir in the lime zest. Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Lay the @Super Soft Whole Wheat Tortillas{4} on a #board{} (two per person), spoon the mixture down the centre of each then roll them up into cylinders.

Drizzle a little oil over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the tortillas. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge downwards so they don't unroll. Spoon the @creme fraiche{112.5%g} over the top in dollops and then spread it out evenly. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} on top, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, squeeze the lime juice into a large #bowl{}. Add the @honey{15%ml} and @olive oil{120%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Whisk together with a #fork{} and your dressing is made! Halve the @cucumber{1/2}, scrape out the seeds with a #teaspoon{} (discard the seeds) and chop the flesh into 1cm chunks.

When the enchiladas are cooked, remove from the oven and leave to cool slightly for ~{2%minutes}. Toss the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1} and cucumber in the dressing. Serve the enchiladas on #plates{} with the salad alongside. Enjoy!